      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candles have all burned down to mere stubs of wax, and the silence of this manor is heavier than the stone walls themselves. He is gone... and with him, the very light of my soul has been extinguished. I look into the darkness of the garden and I no longer see shadows; I see a soft, inviting velvet that calls to me. It feels as though my heart is a leaden weight, pulling me down, down into the earth. There is no grace left for me in this waking world, only the hollow ache of a life that has lost its purpose. Is there truly any beauty left for me, or is the only peace left to be found in the quiet of the eternal night?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
